            <h1>Brown-crested Flycatcher &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Statius MÃ¼ller, 1776)</span></h1>

            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>

            <ul class='genus'>

        <a href='/contributor/YBJUQSUJFZ'>Russ Wigh</a>
        </td>
        
        <td>2017-05-10</td>
        <td> 05:00</td>
      
        <td>United States</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=31.8687&long=-109.1882&loc=South+Fork+of+Cave+Creek+Canyon%2C+Chiricahua+Mountains%2C+Cochise+County%2C+Arizona">South Fork of Cave Creek Canyon, Chiricahua Mountains, Cochise County, Arizona</a>
        </td>
        <td>1600</td>
        <td>call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>This was originally posted as Ash-throated Flycatcher dawn song. After some consideration from 3 experienced SW USA recordists and my own homework it was determined to be Brown-crested Flycatcher.  Ash-throated can be briefly heard in the background. At 0500 there is no light.  The microphones were set on a berm in NOS configuration at the end of a parking area.  This is an excerpt of a 38 minute recording.  This individual called for several minutes in the original recording which can be heard at https://soundcloud.com/russ-wigh/south-fork-cave-creek-az-dawn.</p>

<p>bird-seen:no</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Brown-crested Flycatcher &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Statius MÃ¼ller, 1776)</span></h1>

            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>

            <ul class='genus'>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Interaction calls, definitely three birds involved in the interaction, possibly family group labeled at the time, but I don't hear any obvious juvenile calls now, so I'm even less sure, and suspect it was three adults; anyway, some complicated interaction, but with no long song-call type vocalizations; 3rd vocalization of these birds today</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

        <td>
        <span class='common-name'><a href='/species/Myiarchus-tyrannulus'>Brown-crested Flycatcher</a></span> (<span class='scientific-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus magister</span>)
        </td>

        1:43
        </td>
        <td>
        <a href='/contributor/KZYUWIRZVH'>Richard E. Webster</a>
        </td>
        
        <td>2012-07-14</td>
        <td> 10:36</td>
      
        <td>United States</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=31.906&long=-109.1543&loc=Portal%2C+Arizona">Portal, Arizona</a>
        </td>
        <td>1400</td>
        <td>call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Interaction calls, definitely three birds involved in the interaction, no juveniles yet, so I'm not sure "who" is involved or what is going on; mostly whip series, but some intense interactions later in the cut, more tremulous, but still strong</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>
<p>   </p></div><a class='fancybox' rel='sono' href='http://www.xeno-canto.org/sounds/uploaded/KZYUWIRZVH/ffts/XC123433-large.png' title='XC123433: Brown-crested Flycatcher (Myiarchus tyrannulus magister) by Richard E. Webster'>[sono]</a></div></td>
                <td><a download='XC123433 - Brown-crested Flycatcher - Myiarchus tyrannulus magister.mp3' href='/123433/download'><img class='icon' src='/static/img/download.png' width='14' height='14'  title='Download file &#039;XC123433-FLYCATC_Bro-cre_c_interact 3 birds Portal 071412 1036.mp3&#039;'></a><a class='tooltip' title='Open a discussion, mail the recordist' href='/new_thread.php?frontID=123433'><img class='icon' width='14' height='14' src='/static/img/discuss.png' alt='discuss icon'/></a><div class='rating'>
        <ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <td>
            <ul id='languages'>
            <li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/cs'>Äesky</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/da'>Dansk</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/de'>Deutsch</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/et'>Eesti</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/en'>English</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/es'>EspaÃ±ol</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/fr'>FranÃ§ais</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/hu'>Magyar</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/it'>Italiano</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/lt'>LietuviÅ³</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/nl'>Nederlands</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/no'>Norsk</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pl'>Polski</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pt'>PortuguÃªs</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pt_BR'>PortuguÃªs do Brasil</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ru'>Ð ÑÑÑÐºÐ¸Ð¹</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/sk'>SlovenÄina</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/fi'>Suomi</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/sv'>Svenska</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ja'>æ¥æ¬èª</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ko'>íêµ­ì´</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/zh_CN'>ç®ä½ä¸­æ</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/zh_TW'>ç¹é«ä¸­æ</a></li>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>a couple of song calls, many whip series</p>

            data-qtip-content="&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#039;/species/Zenaida-asiatica&#039;&gt;White-winged Dove&lt;/a&gt; (Zenaida asiatica)&lt;/li&gt;

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Brown-crested Flycatcher &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Statius MÃ¼ller, 1776)</span></h1>

        <td>call, song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>The first part was a Day-Song/Call (whatever it is, whatever you call it), then a call series;  all of this was the first vocalization series by this bird, given in the riparian, after giving dawn song in the mesquite scrub earlier</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Brown-crested Flycatcher &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Statius MÃ¼ller, 1776)</span></h1>

            <ul class='genus'>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

        <td>
        <a href='/contributor/TPPMFWJJOY'>Jane Tillman</a>
        </td>
        
        <td>2015-06-02</td>
        <td> 07:30</td>
      
        <td>United States</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=30.1468&long=-97.6244&loc=Travis+County%2C+Texas">Travis County, Texas</a>
        </td>
        <td>150</td>
        <td>call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>No modification. Habitat was mesquite grassland.  I think there were two Brown-crested Flycatchers and they interacted, tussling with each other. Then one flew to a hackberry and the other flew back to the mesquite, where they continued to call.  The reason I say "I think there were two" because there was an outside chance that one was a Western Kingbird, but the sounds I hear don't sound like Western Kingbird, and both birds had the same rufous in underwings and tail. Weather was clear and about 71 degrees. Sunrise was one hour earlier.</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Brown-crested Flycatcher &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Statius MÃ¼ller, 1776)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Tyrannidae'>Tyrannidae</a> (Tyrant Flycatchers)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Myiarchus'>Myiarchus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>tyrannulus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

            <h1>Brown-crested Flycatcher &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Statius MÃ¼ller, 1776)</span></h1>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

<script type='text/javascript'>
function showSpeciesNr(value, data)
{
    jQuery('#species_nr').val(data.species_nr);
    jQuery('#quick-search-bar > form').submit();
    }
    </script>

            <h1>Brown-crested Flycatcher &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Statius MÃ¼ller, 1776)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Tyrannidae'>Tyrannidae</a> (Tyrant Flycatchers)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Myiarchus'>Myiarchus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>tyrannulus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Brown-crested Flycatcher &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Myiarchus tyrannulus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Statius MÃ¼ller, 1776)</span></h1>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Myiarchus_tyrannulus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});
